page.title: 11Halesowen Football Team
page.content:
On Saturday 27th of April 1985, Halesowen Town Football Team went to Wembley to play in the F.A.Vase against Fleetwood Town. Thousands of fans went to support their local team. There was great tension as they kicked off at three o'clock. Halesowen started the match strongly and within ten minutes Geff Moss scored Halesowen's first goal. Then we completely took over and on fifty and eighty minutes Lee Joinsen scored Halesowen's second and third goals. Fleetwood scored a late consolation goal and there was great jubilation at the final whistle. This made up for the defeat in 1983 against V.S.Rugby when Rugby's goal was off-side.
